HEADWORD: Plankton
<hw>Plank"ton</hw> <pr>(pl⟦acr⟧⟦nsm⟧k"t⟦ocr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>plagto`n</grk>, neut. of <grk>plagto`s</grk>
wandering, <grk>pla`zesqai</grk> to wander.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>All the animals and plants, taken collectively, which live at or
near the surface of salt or fresh waters.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Plank*ton"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Planless</ent>⟦br⟧
